column1: #Text=is the largest town in the Crystal Coast region of North Carolina , with a population of 7,691 ( as of 2000 ) .

#Text=Morehead ( as it is usually called ) is not actually in the Outer Banks , being situated on the opposite shore of the Bogue Sound from Atlantic Beach , and is the main gateway to the island of Bogue Banks .
#Text=Visitors will enter the city by car via US-70 , which runs directly through downtown Morehead .
#Text=It 's a straight shot from Greensboro or Raleigh . you can also get here using Hwy-24 .
#Text=There is no public transportation system in Morehead City ; you 'll need a car to get much of anywhere , although there are a number of reliable taxi companies in the area .
#Text=The main downtown thoroughfare is Arendell Street ( pronounced " uh-REN-dull " ; IPA [ ( ə ) . ' r( ʌ ) n. d( ə ) l ] ) .

#Text=The bus station is located at 105 N 13th Street ( +1 252-726-3029 ) if you want to catch a ride to other towns in the area ; you 'll need to call the Carteret County Area Transportation System at 252-240-1043 for a reservation ahead of time .
#Text=The Morehead City waterfront is a pleasant promenade of gift shops and restaurants by the harbor where the fishing boats come to dock .

#Text=Naturally , some of the freshest seafood can be found at the adjacent fish market , but if you 'd rather have someone else prepare it for you , there are plenty of places here where you can find that too .
#Text=Dedicated to promoting public knowledge of , and interest in , the history and culture of Carteret County .
#Text=Features exhibits on coastal history , a research and genealogical library , a museum shop , and a tea store .
#Text=The area visitors ' center is the Crystal Coast Tourism Authority , 3409 Arendell St , +1 252-726-8148 or +1-800-SUNNY-NC ( 786-6962 ) .
#Text=Visit the Carteret County Curb Market , the oldest continuously-operating curb market in North Carolina .
#Text=Open Saturdays from 7:30AM-11:30AM from May through Labor Day .
#Text=Local farmers and fishermen bring fruits and vegetables , seafood , baked goods and flowers for sale .
#Text=A two-hour entertainment show featuring country-music singers and musicians , and dancing .
#Text=A semi-private 18-hole championship course , rated as the area 's best by Golf Digest in 1995 . $ 47 peak season , $ 37 off-season .
#Text=An award-winning dive operation , offering training , repairs , air and nitrox fills , a full line of rental equipment and gear sales , a Divers ’ lodge , and a friendly , knowledgeable staff .
#Text=Trips include wreck diving , shark observation , underwater photography and spearfishing .
#Text=Morehead also hosts several festivals during the year :
#Text=The Carolina Chocolate Festival , +1-877-848-4976 , is held in the Crystal Coast Civic Center for three days during early February .
#Text=Includes chocolate demonstrations from expert chefs , fondue , a baking contest , a champagne and truffles party , a chocolate Sunday brunch , and live entertainment .
#Text=Is held for a week during June .
#Text=Fisherman converge on the area in an attempt to hook the largest blue marlin , or other gamefish , for cash prizes .
#Text=Is held during the first weekend in October to recognize the importance of seafood to eastern North Carolina .

#Text=Along with the opportunity to sample familiar ( " down east " clam chowder , raw oysters and shrimp burgers ) and adventurous ( calamari , marinated eel , sea urchin on a stick ) seafood , the festival features entertainment , sporting events , and a ceremonial blessing of the fishing fleet .
#Text=There 's nothing especially unique to Morehead City ; if you want beach souvenirs , you 'd be better off trying Atlantic Beach or Emerald Isle .
#Text=However , there are quite a few nice gift shops and galleries around town .
#Text=One of the best selections of new and used books in town , if you need something to read on the beach or by the pool .
#Text=They also accept your used books for trade-in .
#Text=Local and regional books , as well as gifts and souvenirs .
#Text=The perfect store for the cooking aficionado ; a wonderful selection of cookware , cookbooks , utensils and kitchen gadgets ranging from indispensable to wacky .
#Text=An old-timey general store in an old Victorian home ; offers gifts , crafts , home accessories , seasonal decorations and a vast selection of sweets , including ice cream .

#Text=Formerly Pizzutti 's in Atlantic Beach , this much-loved restaurant moved to a larger and fancier building , but still serves the same authentic Italian food , including homemade pasta and breads .
#Text=Open for breakfast Sunday to Thursday , and all day Friday and Saturday .
#Text=Delicious shrimpburgers and milkshakes , and amazingly good Pepsi , brought to your window by car hops .
#Text=Open daily for lunch and dinner ; closed between Thanksgiving and early February .
#Text=Originally a waterfront seafood market ( in 1938 ) , now serving traditional broiled and fried seafood dishes at reasonable prices .
#Text=It 's a very popular local restaurant that seats 600 , with lovely views of the sound through its large dining-room windows .
#Text=Their complimentary Tar Heel hushpuppies are legendary , and try the homemade chowder .
#Text=There 's still a market next door if you want to buy your own fresh ( and sanitary ) fish .
#Text=, 1008 Arendell St ( in the same building as the History Place ) , ☏ +1 252-240-2800 .
#Text=The shop sells over 120 fine teas and tea-related gifts , and there 's a little cafe where you can have a light lunch or high tea .
#Text=Do n't miss the authentic Devonshire cream tea .
#Text=Serves wonderful dishes prepared with fresh local seafood along with modern , visually stimulating plates ranging from pork chops to steaks .
#Text=Excellent wine menu and usually features local artists on the walls .
#Text=Down on the waterfront , serves up much of the same upscale seafood that is found on the coast .
#Text=Featuring Carteret Catch dishes every night prepared with fish caught that day .
#Text=Steaks and rack of lamb are also great .
#Text=Nothing fancy here , just good country cooking at a very good price .
#Text=A good breakfast buffet at a good price .
#Text=New York Style Pizza done right - if you do n't want to spend a fortune every night eating fresh seafood , you ca n't miss with anything on their menu .
